> **Status:** Pre-Implementation Planning  
> **Version:** 1.0  
> **Date:** 2026-06-16  
> **Architect:** Antigravity (Principal Engineer)

---

## 1. Executive Summary

Project JARVIS is a **local-first, autonomous AI operating system** — not a chatbot. It is a persistent cognitive entity with multi-agent collaboration, long-term memory, computer control, voice interaction, self-improvement, and an eventual proprietary foundation model (MYTHOS). This document covers all planning deliverables before a single line of production code is written.

---

## 2. Contradictions & Issues Found in Specification

> [!CAUTION]
> These must be resolved before implementation begins.

| # | Issue | Resolution |
|---|-------|-----------|
| 1 | **DESi** is not a Python AI library — it's the Dark Energy Spectroscopic Instrument. The spec likely refers to a research multi-agent framework. | Treat DESi as a placeholder; use **OpenHands** or a custom agentic discovery framework instead. |
| 2 | **MiroFish** is a swarm-simulation/prediction engine, not a memory or orchestration tool. It has a narrow use-case (social prediction). | Use MiroFish only for simulation/scenario testing. Remove from core runtime. |
| 3 | **Page-Agent** (Alibaba) is a browser-embedded copilot SDK, not a general agent framework. | Use Page-Agent for web UI control only; not as an agent backbone. |
| 4 | **OpenMythos** is a research-only RDT implementation, not production-ready. | Use as inspiration/reference for MYTHOS architecture only. |
| 5 | "Zero-cost" + Neo4j + Qdrant simultaneously: Neo4j Community is free; Qdrant is fully open-source. Both can run locally. | Use Neo4j Community + Qdrant self-hosted. ✅ |
| 6 | TinyGrad vs PyTorch: TinyGrad lacks ecosystem maturity for production training pipelines. | Use **PyTorch** for MYTHOS training; TinyGrad for experimental prototypes only. |
| 7 | "Controlled self-improvement" + "branch→test→benchmark→verify→merge" implies git-based workflow for prompt/workflow changes. | Implement a `JarvisGit` abstraction layer over standard git. |
| 8 | Whisper.cpp cannot reliably serve as a wake-word engine (latency, efficiency). | Use **openWakeWord** for wake-word detection, Whisper.cpp for STT only. |
| 9 | Specifying 11 "brains" and 10 "agents" separately creates ambiguity — brains ≈ capability modules, agents = active reasoning entities. | Brains = service modules. Agents = LangGraph nodes that USE brain services. |
| 10 | "MYTHOS must not be the system" — but MYTHOS is the LLM backbone. | MYTHOS slot is pluggable. System uses Ollama/llama.cpp in early phases. |

