### 4.2 Brain Modules (Service Layer)

| Brain | Responsibility | Core Libraries |
|-------|---------------|----------------|
| **Executive Brain** | Goal decomposition, authority, final decisions | LangGraph, Ollama |
| **Research Brain** | Web search, document analysis, fact gathering | Crawl4AI, Page-Agent, DuckDuckGo API |
| **Memory Brain** | All memory types, retrieval, consolidation | Qdrant, Neo4j, SQLite |
| **Learning Brain** | Skill acquisition, pattern recognition, feedback | PyTorch, SentencePiece |
| **Computer Brain** | OS control, file ops, app launching | PyAutoGUI, subprocess, watchdog |
| **Voice Brain** | STT, TTS, wake word, streaming conversation | openWakeWord, Whisper.cpp, MisoTTS |
| **Coding Brain** | Code generation, review, execution, testing | OpenHands, subprocess sandbox |
| **Security Brain** | Action validation, threat assessment, audit | custom rule engine |
| **Planner Brain** | Task graphs, scheduling, dependency resolution | LangGraph, networkx |
| **Critic Brain** | Quality evaluation, self-critique, revision | LangGraph conditional edges |
| **Observer Brain** | System monitoring, anomaly detection, logging | psutil, structlog |

### 4.3 Agent Roles (Active Reasoning Entities)

Each agent is a **LangGraph StateGraph node** that calls Brain services:

```python
# Agent message protocol
class AgentMessage(TypedDict):
    id: str                    # UUID
    from_agent: str            # Sender name
    to_agent: str              # Recipient name / "broadcast"
    message_type: str          # "task"|"result"|"critique"|"veto"|"inform"
    payload: dict              # Task/result data
    priority: int              # 1-10
    requires_approval: bool    # HITL flag
    timestamp: str
    parent_task_id: str | None
```

