### 5.2 Database Schemas

**SQLite — episodic_memory**
```sql
CREATE TABLE episodes (
    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp TEXT NOT NULL,
    agent TEXT NOT NULL,
    task_description TEXT,
    action_taken TEXT,
    result TEXT,
    success INTEGER,
    importance_score REAL,
    embedding_id TEXT  -- links to Qdrant
);

CREATE TABLE skills (
    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    name TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    code TEXT,  -- Python callable
    trigger_pattern TEXT,
    success_rate REAL,
    usage_count INTEGER,
    created_at TEXT,
    last_used TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE audit_log (
    id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    timestamp TEXT NOT NULL,
    agent TEXT NOT NULL,
    action_type TEXT NOT NULL,
    action_detail TEXT,
    approved_by TEXT,  -- human / executive_agent
    reversible INTEGER,
    reversal_data TEXT  -- JSON snapshot for undo
);
```

**Neo4j — Knowledge Graph Schema**
```cypher
// Entities
(:Concept {id, name, description, confidence})
(:Entity {id, name, type, source})
(:Skill {id, name, trigger, code_ref})
(:Goal {id, description, status, priority})
(:Experience {id, timestamp, summary, embedding_id})

// Relationships
(e:Experience)-[:USED]->(s:Skill)
(e:Experience)-[:ACHIEVED]->(g:Goal)
(c1:Concept)-[:RELATES_TO {weight}]->(c2:Concept)
(c:Concept)-[:DERIVED_FROM]->(e:Experience)
(g:Goal)-[:DEPENDS_ON]->(g2:Goal)
```

**Qdrant Collections**
```
- jarvis_semantic     : general knowledge embeddings
- jarvis_episodic     : episode summary embeddings
- jarvis_skills       : skill description embeddings
- jarvis_web_cache    : cached research embeddings
```

