## 9. Computer Control Architecture

```python
class ComputerBrain:
    def read_file(path) -> str
    def write_file(path, content) -> AuditedResult
    def execute_shell(cmd, sandbox=True) -> ProcessResult
    def open_application(app_name) -> bool
    def browser_control(instruction) -> PlaywrightResult  # via Page-Agent
    def take_screenshot() -> Image
    def monitor_process(pid) -> ProcessStats
    def create_project(template, path) -> ProjectResult
```

All write/execute operations:
1. Security Brain validates intent
2. Audit log entry created (pre-action)
3. Reversibility snapshot taken (where possible)
4. Action executed
5. Audit log updated (post-action with result)

